From: xdna-emu project
Subject: Make m_dev_fd and m_driver protected in platform_drv

The emulator's platform_drv_emu subclass needs write access to m_dev_fd
so that drv_open() can replace the real DRM device fd with a memfd_create
fd.  The base class's non-virtual drv_mmap() reads m_dev_fd directly, so
there is no virtual seam to override -- the subclass must set the field.

Apply from the xdna-driver root:
  git apply /path/to/xdna-driver-platform-protected.patch

--- a/src/shim/platform.h
+++ b/src/shim/platform.h
@@ -215,7 +215,7 @@ protected:
   bool
   load_bo_info(uint32_t key, bo_info& info) const;

-private:
+protected:
   std::shared_ptr<const drv> m_driver;

   // Supposed to be set once and used till object is destroyed.
@@ -223,6 +223,7 @@ private:
   mutable int m_dev_fd = -1;
   mutable std::string m_sysfs_root;

+private:
   // Proces-wide drm_bo map to allow retrieving the bo by handle.
   // If a bo is exported, then imported within the same process, we will
   // get back the same bo handle. We can, then, retrieve the bo back
